-- | The audit-record half of the paid quote verifier. Where
-- `DataStandard.QuoteVerifierAuditV1` records a free verification,
-- `PaidQuoteVerifier_VerifyAndPay` also settles a fee, so the record an auditor
-- inspects must attest not only that the quote verified but that its fee was
-- paid. `AuditRecord` is a concrete template the paid verify choice creates when a
-- verification succeeds and the producer's `allowsAuditRecords` policy and the
-- caller's request both opt in, turning the pure `VerifiedPayload` plus the
-- settled fee into a durable record. The fee settles whether or not the record
-- is written.
--
-- It carries every field the producer's signature committed to, so an auditor can
-- reproduce the check: the shared `VerificationAudit` evidence
-- (`DataStandard.Utils`) with the validity window and evidence triple, the signed
-- `Quote`, and the signed payment â€” the fee amount, the instrument it was
-- denominated in, and the payee it was credited to. The payment fields are also
-- what an auditor needs to assert the fee obligation was discharged as signed,
-- mirroring the payee cross-check `PaidQuoteVerifier_VerifyAndPay` performs
-- on-ledger. The record is signed by the producer (`audit.distributor`) and
-- observed by the verifying party (`audit.verifier`).
module DataStandard.PaidQuoteVerifierAuditV1 where

import DataStandard.Utils (Quote, VerificationAudit)

import Splice.Api.Token.HoldingV1 (InstrumentId)

-- | The read view of an `AuditRecord` for a paid quote verification. It is the
-- free quote record's evidence and signed `Quote`, extended with the fee the
-- producer signed and the choice settled, so an auditor reading it has every field
-- the signature committed to â€” the validity window and quote, plus the cost and
-- payee â€” and can rebuild the `PaidSignedPayload` to re-check the signature, while
-- also seeing that the signed fee was paid to the signed payee.
data PaidQuoteAuditRecordView = PaidQuoteAuditRecordView with
    audit : VerificationAudit
      -- ^ The evidence shared by every verifier's audit record: the verifier and
      -- distributor parties, the verification and publication timestamps, the
      -- signed `expiresAt`, and the `canonicalHash`/`signature`/`publicKey` triple.
      -- See `VerificationAudit`.
    quote : Quote
      -- ^ The verified quote, copied from the verified result: the signed
      -- `feedId`, `price`, and `priceTime`, part of what the canonical encoding
      -- commits to.
    fee : Decimal
      -- ^ The fee that settled, taken from the producer-signed `Cost.fee`. Since
      -- the fee is committed to by `audit.signature`, an auditor can confirm the
      -- amount paid matches the amount signed.
    instrument : InstrumentId
      -- ^ The instrument the fee was denominated in, taken from the signed
      -- `Cost.instrument`. Identifies the asset the settling transfer moved.
    payee : Party
      -- ^ The recipient the fee was credited to. Equal to both the verifier's
      -- pinned `payee` and the payee the producer signed, since
      -- `PaidQuoteVerifier_VerifyAndPay` requires the two to match before settling.
  deriving (Eq, Show)

-- | The audit-record template for the paid quote verifier. Created by
-- `PaidQuoteVerifier_VerifyAndPay` when a verification succeeds and both the
-- producer's audit policy and the caller's request opt in. It is signed by
-- the producer (`audit.distributor`, the verifier's `oracle`) â€” whose authority is
-- present in the verify choice because the producer signs the verifier contract â€”
-- and observed by the verifying party (`audit.verifier`, the choice's `actor`). A
-- party granted the record through explicit disclosure reads it through
-- `AuditRecord_Fetch`. A breaking change to the recorded evidence is a new `-v2`
-- package.
template AuditRecord with
    audit : VerificationAudit
      -- ^ The shared verification evidence. See `VerificationAudit`.
    quote : Quote
      -- ^ The verified quote the audit record attests to.
    fee : Decimal
      -- ^ The fee that settled, from the producer-signed `Cost.fee`.
    instrument : InstrumentId
      -- ^ The instrument the fee was denominated in, from the signed `Cost.instrument`.
    payee : Party
      -- ^ The recipient the fee was credited to.
  where
    signatory audit.distributor
    observer audit.verifier

    -- | Read the view from a record the caller can see. The read path for a party
    -- that is not a stakeholder of the record: it obtains the contract through
    -- explicit disclosure, which grants visibility but not the authority to
    -- `fetch`, and so reads by exercising this nonconsuming choice, authorised by
    -- the caller alone.
    nonconsuming choice AuditRecord_Fetch : PaidQuoteAuditRecordView
      with
        actor : Party
          -- ^ The party reading the audit record, and the sole controller of the
          -- choice.
      controller actor
      do pure PaidQuoteAuditRecordView with audit, quote, fee, instrument, payee
